  "description": "<section id=\"description\">\n<p>If we calculate $a^2\\bmod 6$ for $0 ≤ a ≤ 5$ we get: 0, 1, 4, 3, 4, 1.</p>\n<p>The largest value of a such that $a^2 ≡ a\\bmod 6$ is $4$.</p>\n<p>Let's call $M(n)$ the largest value of $a &#x3C; n$ such that $a^2 ≡ a (\\text{mod } n)$. So $M(6) = 4$.</p>\n<p>Find $\\sum M(n)$ for $1 ≤ n ≤ {10}^7$.</p>\n</section>",
